locations.description:
At the end of the road there is a large cottage made of thick stone with two, stout stories and a thatch roof. Behind this there is brewery.

The folks here are #Druidical#. 

[Who lives here?]{This is the home of the local Brewmaster, his wife, and their young child. 

Recently, the Brewmaster's nephew and his wife have come to help run the brewery, as it is very succesful.

In addition, three apprentices reside in the attic of the brewery.

*Dog*}

[What do they brew?]{#Ale#}

[What is the layout of the brewery?]{The brew house has a main floor containing several large vats for brewing. Beneath there is an aging cellar that creaks under the weight of the vats above.

Ingredients are stored in side sheds. In the attic of the brewhouse are some cots for the apprentices. 

They brew various ales and beers under the direction of the brewmaster, and they can drink almost anyone except the Brewmaster or his nepher under the table.}

[What loot is there?]{The people here keep but a few copper pieces between them.}

A small house with a nicely painted sign showing a painted shield and a chest of drawers.

The folk here are #Druidical#.

[Who lives here?]{This building is the shop and home of the local cabinet maker, his wife, and two young children.

He has an apprentice, who does most of the rough work, while the proprietor does the fine work and the limning.}

[What services are on offer?]{The cabinet maker will happily do any commissioned work of any sort.

He is quite adept at shield designs and sign work and can fashion almost any sort of furniture.

He is not interested in adventuring, and neither is his assistant.}

[What loot is there?]{A small cache of 18 platinum pieces, 21 gold pieces, and 30 electrum pieces is kept under a rock near the back door.#50 feet of silk rope#}

[Exterior Description]{These well-kept buildings are obviously those of a COWHERDER, and a particular odor is quite noticeable in the area.} 

The farmer, his aged mother, wife, and four children and THREE OLDER SONS stay here.

[What services do they offer?]{They have a dairy farm and make cheese, the trader and the inn take what does not sell to passing merchants, so very little is available to individual purchasers.}

[Exterior Description]{A small, wooden cottage sits on the edge of the forest by a babbling brook. 

Piles and pallets of logs are abound.

Nearby, the base of a large long-felled tree acts as a chopping block.}

[What loot is there hidden?]{In a pouch under the floorboards of this cottage are 9gp, 13ep, 17sp, and 38cp.}

A small hall stands here, recently built of fresh smelling timber.

[What is its purpose?]{Its purpose is to host feasts and gatherings, as well as to provide a venue for council meetings and discussions within the community.}

[What does it look like inside?]{Its unlocked doors swing open invitingly, revealing a spacious interior. A few benches and stools are placed against the bare walls, and at the far end rests a large, plain table. 

On the back wall hangs a tapestry depicting a green field with two acorns above a sheaf of grain—the banner of Hommlet.}
